        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"191359\">@Bryn Rhodes</span> I don't understand why the T is needed:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Agreed, allow the use of the 'T' in a datetime literal to build a partial DateTime:<br>\n@2012T<br>\n@2012-01T<br>\n@2012-01-01T</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 157495111,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1549248180
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>why not just @2012 ?</p>",
        "id": 157495121,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1549248191
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>also for <a href=\"http://gforge.hl7.org/gf/project/fhir/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=20013\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://gforge.hl7.org/gf/project/fhir/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&amp;tracker_item_id=20013\">GF#20013</a></p>",
        "id": 157495184,
        "sender_full_name": "Grahame Grieve",
        "timestamp": 1549248325
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The result type of @2012 is Date, but @2012T is DateTime</p>",
        "id": 157495863,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryn Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1549249395
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Without the T, there's no way to specify that you actually want a DateTime, you'd have to convert it.</p>",
        "id": 157495891,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryn Rhodes",
        "timestamp": 1549249443
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh ok. that makes sense. can we make that clearer in the disposition?</p>",
